			<div id="post-174069" class="post_box grt" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article">
				<div class="headline_area">
					<h2 class="headline" itemprop="name"><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/2015/02/19/zuna-drive-is-an-iphone-case-that-has-a-built-in-car-mount/" rel="bookmark">Zuna drive is an iPhone case that has a built in car mount</a></h2>
					<div class="byline small">
						<span class="post_author_intro">by</span> <span class="post_author" itemprop="author"><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/author/julie/">Julie Strietelmeier</a></span>
						<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2015-02-19" />
						<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2015-02-19" />
						<span class="post_date_intro">on</span> <span class="post_date" title="2015-02-19">February 19, 2015</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="post_content" itemprop="articleBody">
<p><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/zuna.jpg" rel="dofollow"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-174070" src="http://the-gadgeteer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/zuna-600x387.jpg" alt="zuna" width="600" height="387" /></a></p> <p>There are hundreds and maybe even thousands of car mounts on the market for your smartphone. But have you ever seen a phone case that has a car mount built in? Me neither, but the Zuna Drive case for the iPhone 5, 5s, 6 and 6 Plus has this unique and space saving feature. Your iPhone snaps into the protective bumper case and on the back you&#8217;ll find a hook that bends out from the back of the case and hooks securely into the AC vent of your car. The Zuna Drive makes it easy to switch from car to car while always having a quick and easy way to keep your phone in view for GPS and other uses. Available in white, orange, blue and black, the <a href="http://zuna.com/" rel="nofollow">Zuna Drive</a> is priced at $39.99 (you can save 20% by using the checkout code of: TESTDRIVE). The iPhone 5 version is shipping this month, with the iPhone 6 version to follow in April.</p> 				</div>
				<meta itemprop="interactionCount" content="UserComments:0" />
