					<h2 class="headline" itemprop="name"><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/2015/02/16/this-usb-hub-has-so-many-ports-that-it-will-make-your-head-explode/" rel="bookmark">This USB hub has so many ports that it will make your head explode</a></h2>
					<div class="byline small">
						<span class="post_author_intro">by</span> <span class="post_author" itemprop="author"><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/author/julie/">Julie Strietelmeier</a></span>
						<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2015-02-16" />
						<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2015-02-16" />
						<span class="post_date_intro">on</span> <span class="post_date" title="2015-02-16">February 16, 2015</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="post_content" itemprop="articleBody">
<p><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/49porthub.jpg" rel="dofollow"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-173996" src="http://the-gadgeteer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/49porthub-600x450.jpg" alt="49porthub" width="600" height="450" /></a></p> <p>It shouldn&#8217;t come as a huge surprise that I have a LOT of gadgets that charge via USB, but this 49 port USB hub from Brando has enough ports for all of my gadgets and all the gadgets of my friends and family. The hub features 49 ports that supply 0.5 &#8211; 1.5A per port so it can charge smartphones and tablets. The only caveat is that you have to provide the power supply. A 60A 5V PSU is recommended which would be another $30-$50 on top of the price of the hub. The USB 49-Port Hub is will ship next month from <a href="http://usb.brando.com/usb-49-port-hub_p12794c0039d015.html" rel="nofollow">Brando</a>. You can pre-order now for $174.</p> 				</div>
