				<div class="headline_area">
					<h2 class="headline" itemprop="name"><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/2015/02/16/this-travel-laundry-stuff-sack-makes-it-easy-to-separate-clean-from-dirty-clothes-in-your-luggage/" rel="bookmark">This Travel Laundry Stuff Sack makes it easy to separate clean from dirty clothes in your luggage</a></h2>
					<div class="byline small">
						<span class="post_author_intro">by</span> <span class="post_author" itemprop="author"><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/author/janet-cloninger/">Janet Cloninger</a></span>
						<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2015-02-16" />
						<meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2015-02-15" />
						<span class="post_date_intro">on</span> <span class="post_date" title="2015-02-16">February 16, 2015</span>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="post_content" itemprop="articleBody">
<p><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/travel-laundry-stuff-sack.jpg" rel="dofollow"><img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-173979" src="http://the-gadgeteer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/travel-laundry-stuff-sack-600x219.jpg" alt="travel-laundry-stuff-sack" width="600" height="219" /></a></p> <p>The Travel Laundry Stuff Sack from Tom Bihn makes it easy to pack and easy to separate your clean from dirty clothes when you travel.  The Sack is available in two sizes: 11.8&#8243; x 5.5&#8243; x 5.5&#8243; to fit the Tom Bihn Aeronaut 30 bag and 13.8&#8243; x 6.7&#8243; x 6.7&#8243; to fit the Tom Bihn Aeronaut 45 bag.  It&#8217;s made of 200 denier Dyneema®/nylon ultralight ripstop fabric made just for Tom Bihn, and it has two drawstring closures &#8211; one on each end &#8211; and a floating divider.  When you pack, you just put all your clothes in from one end.  As you wear clothes, you put the dirty clothes back in the other end of the Sack.  The floating divider keeps the clean and dirty items separated, and you can quickly tell which is the clean and dirty ends because the drawstrings are color coded.  One is black, the other is red, and you decide which end is for dirty.  The bags are available in Steel, Iberian, Ultraviolet, or Wasabi.  The smaller size is $40, and the larger size of the <a href="http://www.tombihn.com/new/travellaundrystuffsack.html" rel="nofollow">Travel Laundry Stuff Sack</a> is $45 from <a href="http://www.tombihn.com" rel="nofollow">Tom Bihn</a><a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/travel-laundry-stuff-sack.jpg" rel="dofollow"><br /> </a>.</p> 				</div>
				<meta itemprop="interactionCount" content="UserComments:0" />
				<a class="num_comments_link" href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/2015/02/16/this-travel-laundry-stuff-sack-makes-it-easy-to-separate-clean-from-dirty-clothes-in-your-luggage/#commentform" rel="nofollow"><span class="num_comments">0</span> comments</a>
				<div class="post_cats" itemprop="keywords">
					<span class="post_cats_intro">Posted in:</span>
					<a href="http://the-gadgeteer.com/category/bags-2/" rel="category tag">Bags</a>,
